{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771596181,"nonce":"shGjmVt567MQwXYJKjKRCd/PFAI=","title":"Client-side validation blocks borrower form when switching from student to employee","message":"When creating a borrower via /verwaltung/new, the client-side validation library (Hyperform, hf-* classes) sets a custom validity error on the student_id field ('Studierende müssen ihre Martikelnummer angeben'). When the borrower type is changed from student to employee, the student_id field becomes hidden and non-required, but Hyperform's setCustomValidity state persists. This blocks form submission via requestSubmit().\n\nDiscovered during E2E browser testing where the borrower_type select was changed programmatically. Needs investigation whether this also affects real users interacting with the dropdown normally, since the validation library may hook into different events.\n\nReproduction:\n1. Go to /verwaltung/new\n2. Leave borrower type as 'student' (default)\n3. Switch to 'employee'\n4. Fill all other fields\n5. Submit -- may be blocked by stale custom validity on hidden student_id field\n\nPre-existing bug, present on main.","files":null}]}